    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genre of film obsessed with bringing to the screen sexual, exploitive, and typically horror-oriented subject matter. Grindhouse films are typically bloody, low-budget, and aimed at a young adult audience.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052803/Muller and Faris, Grindhouse (1996)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filmgenre dat zich concentreert op het in beeld brengen van seksuele, exploiterende en meestal horrorachtige onderwerpen. Grindhouse-films zijn meestal bloederig, low budget en gericht op jonge volwassenen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>耽溺於將色情、剝削和典型恐怖取向的主題搬上螢光幕的電影類型。剝削電影通常血腥且以低成本製成，並針對年輕觀眾所拍攝。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
